<b>OPENSTREETMAP HUMANITARIAN TEAM DEVELOPMENT PROJECT
CUSTOMIZED VERSION OF POTLATCH2 EDITOR WITH HUMANITARIAN PRESETS</b>
at http://pierzen.dev.openstreetmap.org/hotpotlatch2/potlatch2.html

For the Development Phase, we edit on the api06.dev.openstreetmap.org
server where there is minimal data for testing new Applications.
You cannot save unless you have an account on the api06 Dev Server. 

====================================================================
<b>Sources</b>

This repository includes the source files necessary to customize the
Potlatch2 editor, adding the Humanitarian Presets to the menu items.
A section at the end of map_features.xml contains features specific to
Humanitarian tags.

Dependencies :
The files have to be copied in the root of a fresh installation
of the Potlach2 Editor.

To test on api6.dev.openstreetmap.org Server :
- Open an account on that server
- Register the customized version of Potlach2 under Settings /Oauth.
- Indicate latitude and longitude coordinates for an area where there
  is test data on the api06 Dev Server. 
  
